        "notes": [
          "1. ALL WOOD FRAMING SHALL BE DOUGLAS FIR-LARCH NO. 2 OR BETTER.",
          "2. ALL NAILING SHALL CONFORM TO THE LATEST EDITION OF THE UNIFORM BUILDING CODE.",
          "3. ALL FRAMING LUMBER IN CONTACT WITH CONCRETE OR MASONRY SHALL BE PRESSURE TREATED.",
          "4. ALL SHEAR WALLS SHALL BE NAILED WITH 8d COMMON NAILS AT 6\" O.C. AT PANEL EDGES AND 12\" O.C. IN FIELD.",
          "5. ALL ANCHOR BOLTS SHALL BE 5/8\" DIAMETER WITH 7\" MINIMUM EMBEDMENT INTO CONCRETE.",
          "6. ALL POST BASES AND BEAM HANGERS SHALL BE SIMPSON STRONG-TIE OR APPROVED EQUAL.",
          "7. ALL STRUCTURAL STEEL SHALL CONFORM TO ASTM A36.",
          "8. ALL WELDING SHALL BE PERFORMED BY A CERTIFIED WELDER.",
          "9. CONTRACTOR SHALL VERIFY ALL DIMENSIONS AND CONDITIONS AT THE JOB SITE.",
          "10. CONTRACTOR SHALL NOTIFY THE ENGINEER OF ANY DISCREPANCIES BEFORE PROCEEDING WITH WORK.",
          "11. SEE STRUCTURAL GENERAL NOTES FOR ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS."
        ]
      },
